pyCIMS model reader¶

The code here reads ../pyCIMS_model_description.xlsm and extracts the 'Model' sheet into a Pandas DataFrame. The dataframe is then split and the referenced parts are organized in dictionaries, see below.

Later, the individual node and tech frames are analyzed for service connectivity information, enabling the construction of a graph.

Display Nodes and Technologies¶

node_dfs contains a dictionary giving the DataFrames that hold the relevant rows for each node, without Technology info
tech_dfs contains a dictionary for each node naming the technologies and holding the relevant rows in a DF
